      • checkWhetherArray

        void checkWhetherArray(SyntaxUnit use)
        Description copied from class: Declaration
        checkWhetherArray: Utility method to check whether this Declaration is really an array. The compiler must check that a name is used properly; for instance, using an array name a in "a()" or in "x=a;" is illegal. This is handled in the following way:
        • When a name a is found in a setting which implies that should be an array (i.e., in a construct like "a["), the parser will first search for a's declaration d.
        • The parser will call d.checkWhetherArray(this).
        • Every sub-class of Declaration will implement a checkWhetherArray. If the declaration is indeed an array, checkWhetherArray will do nothing, but if it is not, the method will give an error message.
        Examples
        GlobalArrayDecl.checkWhetherArray(...)
        will do nothing, as everything is all right.
        FuncDecl.checkWhetherArray(...)
        will give an error message.
        Specified by:
        checkWhetherArray in class Declaration
